    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="953"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d953">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.67/7–2744</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Soviet Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Soviet Government expresses its gratitude for the reply of the Government of
                    the United States of July 22 on the Turkish question.</p>
                <pb facs="0905" n="893" xml:id="pg_893"/>
                <p>The Soviet Government remains of the opinion that the position taken by the
                    Turkish Government in respect to Germany is unsatisfactory and comes to much too
                    late discussions of those or other half-measures, which do not have any
                    essential significance in the present situation. In view of this the Soviet
                    Government considers it necessary to discontinue pressure on the Turkish
                    Government and leave it entirely to its own will.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-27">July 27,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
